HEADWORD: Mare
<hw>Mare</hw> <pr>(m⟦acir⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>mere</ets>, AS. <ets>mere</ets>, <ets>myre</ets>, fem of AS.
<ets>mearh</ets> horse, akin to D. <ets>merrie</ets> mare, G.
<ets>m⟦aum⟧hre</ets>, OHG. <ets>marah</ets> horse, <ets>meriha</ets>
mare, Icel. <ets>marr</ets> horse, OCelt. <ets>marka</ets> (Pausan. 19,
19,4), Ir. <ets>marc</ets>, W. <ets>march</ets>. Cf.
<er>Marshal</er>.]</ety> <def>The female of the horse and other equine
quadrupeds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mare</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mare
<hw>Mare</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>mara</ets> incubus; akin to
OHG. & Icel. <ets>mara</ets>; cf. Pol. <ets>mora</ets>, Bohem.
<ets>m⟦uring⟧ra</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Sighing,
suffocative panting, intercepted utterance, with a sense of pressure
across the chest, occurring during sleep; the incubus; -- obsolete,
except in the compound <xex>nightmare</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will ride thee o' nights like the <qex>mare</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marechal Niel</ent>⟦br⟧
